                        <provenance type="found" when="1978">Discovered by Con Manning in the late 1970s (Manning and Moore 1997, 371). This second ogham stone is situated just above present ground level, built into the external face of the north wall of the nave, immediately east of the north doorway of the ruined church, and is in a horizontal position (Manning and Moore 1997, 371).</provenance>
                        <provenance type="observed">In situ. Built into lower north wall of the nave.</provenance>
